    "attributes": {
        "action": "All issues get voted by the UK population - MPs will just debate the issues",
        "additional_details": "MPs would not be able to vote on issues, just debate them in HoC. I think this should be the future for our democracy.",
        "background": "One vote every five years is no longer democracy in an internet age. The UK needs to be the first parliament that hands the voting of all issues into the hands of all UK residents and passport holders who are over 16. ",
